very hour using a time-weighted average of the premium between mark price and index price. The exchange's Cosmos appchain enables faster settlement and lower gas costs compared to Ethereum-based DEXs. Funding payments occur automatically through the protocol's smart contracts, with rates typically ranging from -0.01% to 0.01% per hour depending on market sentiment."}]]}],"$L3",["$L4","$L5","$L6"],"$L7"]}],"$L8"]}]]}],["$L9","$La"],"$Lb"]}],"loading":null,"isPartial":false}
3:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","APT","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"APT represents Aptos blockchain's native token, offering exposure to a major Layer 1 ecosystem competing with Ethereum and Solana. The pair's moderate volatility and established market presence make it suitable for funding rate strategies. dYdX's 1-hour funding intervals provide more frequent arbitrage opportunities compared to 8-hour cycles on centralized exchanges."}]]}]
4:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"APT/USDT funding rates on dYdX have historically shown correlation with broader L1 sentiment and Aptos ecosystem developments. During major network upgrades or partnership announcements, funding rates often skew positive as traders take long positions anticipating price appreciation. The pair typically exhibits lower funding volatility compared to newer altcoins, with rates staying within ±0.005% per hour during normal market conditions. Extended periods of negative funding have coincided with broader crypto market downturns and reduced interest in alternative Layer 1 solutions."}]]}]
5:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"dYdX's hourly funding creates 24 opportunities per day for rate arbitrage compared to 3 on traditional 8-hour exchanges. Traders can capitalize on funding rate differences between dYdX and centralized venues like Binance or OKX by going long where rates are negative and short where positive. The exchange's Cosmos appchain architecture enables faster position adjustments and lower transaction costs. Cross-exchange arbitrage becomes particularly profitable during periods of high APT volatility when funding rates diverge significantly between venues."}]]}]
6:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"dYdX V4's migration to Cosmos introduces new technical risks including potential validator issues and cross-chain bridge vulnerabilities. Lower liquidity compared to major centralized exchanges can result in wider bid-ask spreads and increased slippage for larger positions. The exchange's newer technology stack may experience occasional downtime or bugs affecting order execution during critical market moments. Traders should also consider the regulatory uncertainty around decentralized derivatives and potential future compliance requirements that could impact platform accessibility."}]]}]
7:["$","$Lc",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often are APT funding rates calculated on dYdX?","answer":"dYdX calculates and settles APT/USDT funding rates every hour, providing 24 funding events per day. This frequent settlement creates more arbitrage opportunities compared to the standard 8-hour cycles used by most centralized exchanges."},{"question":"What are typical APT funding rate ranges on dYdX?","answer":"APT funding rates on dYdX typically range from -0.01% to +0.01% per hour during normal market conditions. During high volatility or significant Aptos ecosystem news, rates can extend to ±0.02% per hour or higher."},{"question":"Can I arbitrage APT funding rates between dYdX and CEXs?","answer":"Yes, you can arbitrage funding rate differences by taking opposite positions on dYdX versus centralized exchanges. The strategy works best when there's a significant rate differential and sufficient liquidity on both venues to execute trades efficiently."},{"question":"What risks are specific to trading APT on dYdX V4?","answer":"Key risks include the platform's migration to Cosmos creating potential technical issues, lower liquidity compared to major CEXs, and the experimental nature of the sovereign appchain architecture. Smart contract risks and potential validator problems also add complexity compared to traditional exchanges."}]}]
